   Here is the 89-11 roll call by which the
Senate Tuesday approved air pollution controls on automobiles,
factories and power plants.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to approve the bill while a
no vote was a vote to defeat the legislation.
   Voting yes were 50 Democrats and 39 Republicans.
   Voting no were 5 Democrats and 6 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
